WEEDEN ISLAND (1800-950 BP); FORT WALTON (950-350 BP)
Previous investigations were supported by this survey and showed that both Wakulla Check Stamped and a poss. Pensacola/Fort Walton Incised.
Diagnostic artifacts include: Weeden Island 1800-950 B.P., Fort Walton 950-350 B.P.

Multiple prehistoric temporal components evidenced by Mississippian, Norwood, Deptford, and Weeden Island diagnostic ceramic sherds. Non-naturally occurring gravel mixed into horizons from 0-110cmbs indicates substantial disturbance of stratigraphy.
